---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.jawaharprasad.com/" />

    <title>Jawahar Prasad, Senior Director of Engineering, Tekion</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Jawahar Prasad architects AI dev productivity at scale at Tekion, including the measurement framework that doesn't depend on AI lineage or surveys." />

    <!-- Open Graph (LinkedIn / Twitter sharing) -->
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://www.jawaharprasad.com/" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Jawahar Prasad, Senior Director of Engineering, Tekion" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Builds AI dev productivity at scale, and the measurement framework that doesn't depend on AI lineage or surveys." />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://www.jawaharprasad.com/jawahar.jpg" />

    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Jawahar Prasad, Senior Director of Engineering, Tekion" />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Builds AI dev productivity at scale, and the measurement framework that doesn't depend on AI lineage or surveys." />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://www.jawaharprasad.com/jawahar.jpg" />

    <!-- Favicon: minimal text-based via SVG (no separate file needed) -->
    <link rel="icon" href="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 100 100'%3E%3Ctext y='80' font-size='90' font-family='system-ui,sans-serif' font-weight='700'%3EJ%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E" />
  </head>

  <body class="bg-white text-slate-900 antialiased">
    <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">

      <header class="mb-16 flex items-center gap-6">
        <img
          src="/jawahar.jpg"
          alt="Jawahar Prasad"
          width="128"
          height="128"
          class="w-28 h-28 sm:w-32 sm:h-32 rounded-full object-cover ring-1 ring-slate-200 flex-shrink-0"
        />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Jawahar Prasad</h1>
          <p class="mt-1 text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-600">
            Senior Director of Engineering · Tekion · Architecting AI dev productivity at scale
          </p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section aria-labelledby="lead" class="mb-12">
        <p id="lead" class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold leading-snug tracking-tight text-slate-900">
          I build AI dev productivity at scale, and the measurement framework that doesn't depend on AI lineage or surveys.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-800 mb-16">
        <p>
          Currently Senior Director of Engineering at Tekion, architecting <strong>ORBIT</strong>: Tekion's agentic AI dev-productivity platform running across thousands of repositories (700+ microservices), used across engineering, QA, and product. ORBIT replaced <strong>PDAF</strong> (Persona-Driven AI Framework), the prompt-driven AI agent framework I shipped in 2025. PDAF produced the results Augment Code documented in their December 2025 customer feature: 60% reduction in merge time (3 days to 1 day), +21% MR volume at the same headcount.
        </p>
        <p>
          ORBIT's sub-systems: <strong>DeepContext</strong> (hybrid retrieval over Jira, Confluence, code, PRs), <strong>Central</strong> (agentic orchestration with sandboxed execution), and <strong>CPI</strong> (Composite Productivity Index, a measurement framework introduced in a paper in development). <strong>AIR</strong> (incident-response research direction) is in early preview.
        </p>
        <p>
          Twenty-one years building large-scale platforms; ~16 of them in ML, search, shopping, and AI. Yahoo!, Jabong, Flipkart (doubled ads revenue, Best People Manager 2018), Amazon (Recommendations and Personalization). Founding team of what became <strong>Whatfix</strong> (2010, left after 13 months before product-market fit).
        </p>
        <p>
          I write about AI-native developer productivity at scale: the builder, leader, and measurer angle in one voice.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600">
          Bay Area · originally Bangalore.
        </p>
      </section>

      <nav aria-label="More pages" class="mb-16 flex flex-wrap gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-lg">
        <a href="/about" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4 transition">More about me &rarr;</a>
        <a href="/leadership" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4 transition">How I lead &rarr;</a>
      </nav>

      <section aria-labelledby="work" class="mb-16">
        <h2 id="work" class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-4">Selected work</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg">
          <li>
            <a href="https://leaddev.com/community/jawahar-prasad" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4 transition" rel="noopener">
              LeadDev: How Tekion enabled 1,300 employees to work with agents
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://www.augmentcode.com/blog/introducing-augment-code-review" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4 transition" rel="noopener">
              Augment Code customer feature, Dec 2025: 60% merge-time reduction at scale
            </a>
          </li>
          <li class="text-slate-500">
            CPI: Measuring AI Impact on Engineering Productivity Without Lineage or Surveys <span class="text-sm">(paper in development)</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="elsewhere" class="mb-16">
        <h2 id="elsewhere" class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-4">Elsewhere</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg">
          <li>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jawaharprasad" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4 transition" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://github.com/jawahar4k" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4 transition" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="#contact"
              data-user="hi"
              data-domain="jawaharprasad.com"
              class="email-link text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4 transition"
            >Click to reveal email</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="subscribe" class="mb-16">
        <h2 id="subscribe" class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 mb-4">Get future posts</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          No newsletter yet. I'm publishing on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jawaharprasad" class="underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4">LinkedIn</a> for now. Want a heads-up when I launch one? <a
            href="#subscribe"
            data-user="hi"
            data-domain="jawaharprasad.com"
            data-subject="Subscribe"
            class="email-link underline decoration-slate-300 hover:decoration-slate-900 underline-offset-4"
          >Click to reveal my email address</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <script is:inline>
        // Click-to-reveal email obfuscation. The real address never appears in the static HTML
        // or before the human clicks. First click reveals + sets up mailto:; second click sends.
        document.querySelectorAll('a.email-link').forEach((el) => {
          el.addEventListener('click', function (e) {
            if (!el.dataset.revealed) {
              e.preventDefault();
              const addr = el.dataset.user + '@' + el.dataset.domain;
              const subject = el.dataset.subject ? '?subject=' + encodeURIComponent(el.dataset.subject) : '';
              el.href = 'mailto:' + addr + subject;
              el.textContent = addr;
              el.dataset.revealed = 'true';
            }
          });
        });
      </script>

      <footer class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-slate-200 text-sm text-slate-500">
        © Jawahar Prasad · jawaharprasad.com
      </footer>

    </main>
  </body>
</html>
